Package com.cafean.jobstream.tracker

Class TaskRec

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.jobstream.tracker.TaskRec
  • public class TaskRec
extends java.lang.Object
    Utility class used to hold records for the TASK Database Table. The TASK Table manages the list of Tasks for a each Job Stream.

      • status

        public java.lang.String status
        The task status. Active - A task that is currently executing and communicating the the stream manager. Running - A task that is currently executing but is not necessarily communicating with the stream manager. Unprocessed - A task that has not yet been evaluated by the Stream Manager during initialization. Blocked - A task that is waiting for other tasks to complete. Completed - A task that has completed without a failure being reported. Excluded - A task that was excluded from execution based on input file conditionals. Failed - A task that has completed but a failure was reported. Precluded - A task that was excluded from execution because a prerequisite task was excluded. Queued - A task that has been submitted to the queuing system but has not connected to the stream manager. Waiting - A task that is ready to be executed but has not yet been submitted.
